 took one of the glasses, and holding it carefully in front of him, mimicking the swaying level of the liquid with his eyebrows, began slowly to mount the stairs.

When he had disappeared round the bend she began with exaggerated care to peel the thin paper from her straw. 'What a boor!' said her mother loudly, and the daughter felt the kind of satisfaction you get when you find in the dictionary the meaning of a foreign term you have already guessed. 'That's not a real person,' continued her mo